The Cauterist Synod has resumed unauthorized re-firing ceremonies in the kiln district, using the administrative confusion from recent ledger recovery operations as cover. The Midgaard postmaster, acting under Violet Compact registry authority, requires disruption of the current ceremonial cycle before it validates new Synod territorial claims along the Scorching Sands approach. Eliminate one cauterist acolyte, one brand cantor, and one re-firing deacon to break the cycle.
The Cauterist re-firing ceremony has been disrupted. The Midgaard postmaster has recorded the disruption as a Violet Compact compliance victory and forwarded evidence of unauthorized re-firing to the Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger for inclusion in the pending jurisdictional violation report. The current ceremonial cycle cannot proceed without completing the sacramental sequence.

